### Base URL — must match `dotnet run` / launchSettings "Now listening on:" (example below).
### Use Development so SQLite is created locally and cookies work over HTTP (appsettings.Development.json).
@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:5000

### Swagger UI (Development only)
# @name swagger
GET {{baseUrl}}/swagger/index.html

### Register — use a fresh email each run (duplicate email → 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json
X-Client-Id: postman-test-client

{
  "email": "driver-{{$guid}}@example.com",
  "password": "TestPass123!",
  "phoneNumber": "+15551234567"
}

### Login — same password as register above; change email to match
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json
X-Client-Id: postman-test-client

{
  "email": "driver-REPLACE_WITH_EMAIL@example.com",
  "password": "TestPass123!",
  "clientId": "postman-test-client"
}

### Refresh — send cookies from register/login (Postman: enable cookie jar for this host).
### Body.csrfToken must match the csrfToken field from the last auth JSON response.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "csrfToken": "PASTE_CSRF_FROM_JSON_RESPONSE"
}

### Verify OTP — requires Authorization: Bearer <access_token> from partial login/MFA flow
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/otp/verify
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json
X-Client-Id: postman-test-client

{
  "code": "123456",
  "purpose": "NewDeviceVerification"
}

### Logout — revokes current refresh token and clears auth cookies
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout
